{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place cheese in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic cloves and 10 g extra virgin olive oil in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then sauté <nobr>2 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add bread and sauté without measuring cup <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, line Varoma tray with baking paper with enough to go 2 cm up the sides. Transfer sautéed garlic bread to Varoma dish and set aside.","Place spinach, 10 g extra virgin olive oil, eggs and ½ tsp salt in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>30 sec\/speed 5.5<\/nobr>. Transfer spinach-egg mixture to lined Varoma tray, spread to the borders, sprinkle with reserved grated cheese and insert Varoma tray in Varoma dish.","Place onions, carrots, 30 g extra virgin olive oil, tomatoes, 1-2 basil leaves, water, vegetable stock paste and ½ tsp salt in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Insert simmering basket and add mixed vegetables to it. Set Varoma in position and cook <nobr>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma. With aid of baking paper lining, roll up the spinach omelette, keeping it wrapped in the baking paper. Meanwhile remove simmering basket using spatula, transfer cooked vegetables to a shallow serving dish, season with salt to taste and stir. Unwrap the spinach omelette and cut in slices (approx. 2 cm). Transfer slices to serving dish with vegetables and keep warm. Transfer tomato soup to a serving bowl, add reserved steamed garlic bread to the soup, drizzle with some extra virgin olive oil and garnish with roughly torn basil leaves. Serve the soup hot as a starter and the rolled omelette warm as a main dish, with the ratatouille vegetables on the side."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["60 g medium-hard cheese (e.g. Gruyère, Emmental, Cheddar), cut in pieces","2 garlic cloves","50 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for serving","50 g stale bread roll, cut in pieces (1-2 cm),","200 g frozen chopped spinach, defrosted","4 eggs","1 tsp salt, plus extra to taste","50 g onions, cut in halves","50 g carrots, cut in pieces","700 g ripe tomatoes, cut in pieces,","6 - 8 fresh basil leaves","500 g water","1 heaped tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade","400 g mixed vegetables (e.g. peppers, courgettes, aubergines), cut in pieces (2-3 cm)"]}],"id":"r89795","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-dsJtV__shiI\/XZapkcdCmnI\/AAAAAAAAhSM\/xEXugdpSVgEA6sO8jSZSessQzBw4nnUYACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_2fIH1B9_vLZ_ta0o.png","title":"Bread and tomato soup, Rolled spinach omelette and Steamed ratatouille vegetables","publishedAt":"2017-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17 g","fat":"26 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"19 g","calories":"1654 kJ \/ 395 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper","hintsAndTricks":["'Pappa al pomodoro', or bread and tomato soup, is classic comfort food in many Italian homes. While the soup is bubbling away, steam the next soothing course: a spinach and cheese rolled omelette presented in beautiful green spirals, served with hearty Mediterranean vegetables on the side.","For a smooth soup, after removing Varoma and simmering basket in <nobr>step 6,<\/nobr> blend <nobr><strong>1 min\/speed 5-10,<\/strong><\/nobr> <strong>increasing speed gradually.<\/strong> Add the steamed garlic bread and serve as described in <nobr>step 6.<\/nobr>","Replace spinach in the rolled omelette with vegetables of your choice (e.g. cabbage, courgette)."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 5m","4 portions"]}